  "text": "This openness to theoretical multiplicity has demonstrated a better and more reflexive evaluation of important governance features such as power and politics, inclusion and equity [CITATION_1] . This multi-perspective approach might therefore enable conceptual and knowledge gaps to be addressed through reference to other theories but without trying to integrate every theory under one paradigm [CITATION_2] . At the same time, adaptive governance literature has been criticized for being too conceptual, normatively tainted and to have a limited ability to address real-world problems [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] .",
